>> B2: Explain the data structure used to track priority donation.
>> Use ASCII art to diagram a nested donation.  (Alternately, submit a
>> .png file.)

The data structure used to track priority donation in this implementation 
is a linked list (struct list), where each thread maintains a list of threads 
that could potentially donate their priority to it, sorted by priority. 
Specifically, this list contains the highest priority thread waiting for 
each lock held by the current thread. Each thread has the following relevant members:

waiting_lock: A pointer to the lock that the thread is currently waiting on.
original_priority: The base priority of the thread, before any donations.
donations: A list of threads that could potentially donate their priority to this thread. 
           This list contains the highest priority thread waiting for each lock held by the current thread.
donation_elem: A list element used to insert this thread into another thread's donation list.


Nested Priority Donation

Example Scenario
Thread C holds Lock 2.
Thread B tries to acquire Lock 2, which is held by Thread B, and is blocked, so it could donate its priority to Thread C.
Thread A tries to acquire Lock 1 but is blocked, so it could donate its priority to Thread B.


  
Thread A [original_priority: 30, priority: 30]
  |
  |---> Lock 1 (held by B)
         |
         v
Thread B [original_priority: 20, priority: 30]
  |
  |---> Lock 2 (held by C)
         |
         v
Thread C [original_priority: 10, priority: 30]


1) Thread C acquires lock 2 since it currently has no owner 

    Lock 2 (held by C)
         |
         v
Thread C [original_priority: 10, priority: 10]

2) Thread B tries to acquire lock 2 but it is held by thread C so it is put on the waiters list and list of donors for 
thread C as it has the highest priority amonst the chain of waiters

Thread B [original_priority: 20, priority: 20]
  |
  |---> Lock 2 (held by C)
         |
         v
Thread C [original_priority: 10, priority: 20]

3) Thread A tries to acquire lock 1 but it is held by thread B so it is put on the waiters list and list of donors for 
thread B as it has the highest priority amonst the chain of waiters. The priority of Thread B gest updated and becomes 30.
Since Thread B is the top donor in the list for Thread C it in turn gets updated to Thread B's current value of 30.

Thread A [original_priority: 30, priority: 30]
  |
  |---> Lock 1 (held by B)
         |
         v
Thread B [original_priority: 20, priority: 30]
  |
  |---> Lock 2 (held by C)
         |
         v
Thread C [original_priority: 10, priority: 30]


